{"video_id": "ziIK8i18pGg", "title": "Daily Evening Bhagavatam Discourse | HH Stoka Krishna Swami | SB 1.15.47-48 | 03-01-2023", "speaker": "HH Stoka Krishna Swami", "youtube_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ziIK8i18pGg", "duration": 861, "segments": [{"start": 0.0, "end": 8.48, "text": " ओम अज्ञानति मिरान्दस्य ज्ञानान्जनिषलाकया चक्षुरुन्मीलितं येनातस्मै श्री गुरवे नमः"}, {"start": 8.48, "end": 16.9, "text": " नमः ओम विष्णु पाधाया कृष्ण प्रेष्ठाय भूतले श्री मते भक्ति वेदान्त स्वामेन्निति नामिने"}, {"start": 16.9, "end": 25.58, "text": " नमस्ते सारस्वते देवे गव्रवाणी प्रचारिने निर्विशेशा शुन्यवादी पाश्चात्यदेशतारिने"}, {"start": 25.58, "end": 34.64, "text": " जय श्री कृष्ण चैतन्या प्रभूनित्यानन्दा श्री अद्वैत गदाधर श्रीवासादी गव्रभक्त वृन्दा"}, {"start": 34.64, "end": 54.540000000000006, "text": " Hare Krishna Hare Krishna Krishna Krishna Hare Hare Hare Rama Hare Rama Rama Rama Hare Hare Om Namo Bhagavate Vasudevaya Narayanam Namaskritya Naramchaiva Narottamam Devim Sarasvatim Vyasam Tato Jayam Udi Rayet"}, {"start": 54.54, "end": 65.98, "text": " In this session we will be discussing from two verses 47 and 48 of the 15th chapter of the first canto Srimad Bhagavatam."}, {"start": 65.98, "end": 81.64, "text": " Tadhyana Udriktaya Bhaktiya Vishuddha Dhisana Pare Tasmin Narayana Pade Ekanta Matayogatim"}, {"start": 81.64, "end": 96.64, "text": " Avapur Duravapamte Asadbhir Vishayatmabhihi Vidhutakalmashasthanam Virajena Atmanayivahee"}, {"start": 96.64, "end": 100.64, "text": " The meaning of these two verses is given together."}, {"start": 100.64, "end": 106.64, "text": " Thus by pure consciousness, due to constant devotional remembrance,"}, {"start": 106.64, "end": 109.64, "text": " they attain the spiritual sky,"}, {"start": 109.64, "end": 111.64, "text": " which is ruled over by the spiritual sky,"}, {"start": 111.64, "end": 114.64, "text": " and by the supreme Narayana, Lord Krishna."}, {"start": 114.64, "end": 121.64, "text": " This is attained only by those who meditate upon the one supreme Lord without deviation."}, {"start": 121.64, "end": 128.64, "text": " This abode of the Lord Sri Krishna, known as Goloka Vrindavana,"}, {"start": 128.64, "end": 134.64, "text": " cannot be attained by persons who are absorbed in the material conception of life."}, {"start": 134.64, "end": 139.64, "text": " One of us, being completely washed of all material contamination,"}, {"start": 139.64, "end": 141.64, "text": " attained that abode,"}, {"start": 141.64000000000001, "end": 146.64000000000001, "text": " in their very same bodies."}, {"start": 146.64000000000001, "end": 148.64000000000001, "text": " This is very significant that"}, {"start": 148.64000000000001, "end": 154.64000000000001, "text": " the Pandavas went back to Godhead in the self-same body."}, {"start": 154.64000000000001, "end": 158.64000000000001, "text": " Generally, at the end of life,"}, {"start": 158.64000000000001, "end": 160.64000000000001, "text": " we quit this body."}, {"start": 160.64000000000001, "end": 164.64000000000001, "text": " We leave behind this material body."}, {"start": 164.64000000000001, "end": 167.64000000000001, "text": " Even those who go back to Godhead,"}, {"start": 167.64000000000001, "end": 169.64000000000001, "text": " generally,"}, {"start": 169.64000000000001, "end": 173.64000000000001, "text": " leave the material body behind."}, {"start": 173.64000000000001, "end": 175.64000000000001, "text": " But the Pandavas,"}, {"start": 175.64000000000001, "end": 177.64000000000001, "text": " in the self-same body,"}, {"start": 177.64000000000001, "end": 179.64000000000001, "text": " they went back to Godhead."}, {"start": 179.64000000000001, "end": 186.64000000000001, "text": " Because they were purified of all material contamination"}, {"start": 186.64000000000001, "end": 193.64000000000001, "text": " by constant devotional remembrance of Krishna."}, {"start": 193.64000000000001, "end": 198.64000000000001, "text": " This is the situation of the pure devotees."}, {"start": 199.64000000000001, "end": 201.64000000000001, "text": " Constantly thinking of Krishna."}, {"start": 201.64000000000001, "end": 204.64000000000001, "text": " Constantly engaged in Krishna's service."}, {"start": 204.64000000000001, "end": 206.64000000000001, "text": " Pure devotional service."}, {"start": 206.64000000000001, "end": 210.64000000000001, "text": " No tinge of any material sense gratification"}, {"start": 210.64000000000001, "end": 212.64000000000001, "text": " in any of their activities."}, {"start": 212.64000000000001, "end": 216.64000000000001, "text": " Such devotees' bodies are all spiritual."}, {"start": 216.64000000000001, "end": 219.64000000000001, "text": " They are not material."}, {"start": 219.64000000000001, "end": 225.64000000000001, "text": " So, Srila Prabhupada explains this point in the purport."}, {"start": 225.64000000000001, "end": 228.64000000000001, "text": " According to Srila Jiva Goswami,"}, {"start": 228.64000000000001, "end": 233.64000000000001, "text": " a person freed from the three modes of material qualities,"}, {"start": 233.64000000000001, "end": 236.64000000000001, "text": " namely goodness, passion and ignorance,"}, {"start": 236.64000000000001, "end": 239.64000000000001, "text": " and situated in transcendence,"}, {"start": 239.64000000000001, "end": 242.64000000000001, "text": " can reach the highest perfection of life"}, {"start": 242.64000000000001, "end": 248.64000000000001, "text": " without change of body."}, {"start": 248.64000000000001, "end": 253.64000000000001, "text": " This is the explanation of one of the previous Acharyas,"}, {"start": 253.64000000000001, "end": 254.64000000000001, "text": " Srila Jiva Goswami."}, {"start": 254.64000000000001, "end": 257.64, "text": " He is one of the six Goswamis of Vrindavan,"}, {"start": 257.64, "end": 260.64, "text": " the direct disciples of Sri Chaitanya Mahaprabhu."}, {"start": 260.64, "end": 262.64, "text": " Srila Jiva Goswami says,"}, {"start": 262.64, "end": 267.64, "text": " a person freed from the three modes of material qualities,"}, {"start": 267.64, "end": 270.64, "text": " goodness, passion and ignorance,"}, {"start": 270.64, "end": 274.64, "text": " and situated in transcendence,"}, {"start": 274.64, "end": 277.64, "text": " can reach the highest perfection of life"}, {"start": 277.64, "end": 280.64, "text": " without change of body."}, {"start": 280.64, "end": 285.64, "text": " So generally we are engaged in one of the three gunas."}, {"start": 287.64, "end": 289.64, "text": " Because we are influenced by the gunas,"}, {"start": 289.64, "end": 291.64, "text": " the material modes."}, {"start": 291.64, "end": 294.64, "text": " So our actions are either sattvic, rajasic or tamasic,"}, {"start": 294.64, "end": 298.64, "text": " or a combination of one or more of these qualities."}, {"start": 298.64, "end": 303.64, "text": " So we have material activities and material reactions,"}, {"start": 303.64, "end": 306.64, "text": " which bind us to this world."}, {"start": 306.64, "end": 312.64, "text": " Now those who are freed from these three qualities,"}, {"start": 312.64, "end": 315.64, "text": " because they are constantly engaged"}, {"start": 315.64, "end": 318.64, "text": " in the pure devotional service,"}, {"start": 328.64, "end": 330.64, "text": " Krishna explains this in the Bhagavad Gita,"}, {"start": 330.64, "end": 332.64, "text": " as Srila Prabhupada will quote later,"}, {"start": 332.64, "end": 334.64, "text": " this very verse,"}, {"start": 334.64, "end": 339.64, "text": " that one who is engaged in pure devotional service,"}, {"start": 339.64, "end": 341.64, "text": " without deviation,"}, {"start": 341.64, "end": 345.64, "text": " such a person is completely free"}, {"start": 345.64, "end": 348.64, "text": " from the influence of all the three gunas."}, {"start": 348.64, "end": 351.64, "text": " All actions of such a person"}, {"start": 351.64, "end": 358.64, "text": " are completely transcendental."}, {"start": 358.64, "end": 359.64, "text": " And further,"}, {"start": 359.64, "end": 361.64, "text": " Srila Prabhupada quotes"}, {"start": 361.64, "end": 364.64, "text": " Sanatana Goswami."}, {"start": 364.64, "end": 365.64, "text": " What does he say?"}, {"start": 365.64, "end": 369.64, "text": " Srila Sanatana Goswami in his Haribhakti Vilas says,"}, {"start": 369.64, "end": 372.64, "text": " that a person,"}, {"start": 372.64, "end": 374.64, "text": " whatever he may be,"}, {"start": 374.64, "end": 376.64, "text": " can attain the perfection"}, {"start": 376.64, "end": 378.64, "text": " of a twice-born brahmana"}, {"start": 378.64, "end": 381.64, "text": " by undergoing the spiritual disciplinary actions"}, {"start": 381.64, "end": 383.64, "text": " under the guidance"}, {"start": 383.64, "end": 386.64, "text": " of a bona fide spiritual master."}, {"start": 392.64, "end": 396.64, "text": " yatha kanchanatam yati"}, {"start": 396.64, "end": 401.64, "text": " kamsyam rasa-vidhanatah"}, {"start": 404.64, "end": 410.64, "text": " tatha deeksha-vidhanena"}, {"start": 410.64, "end": 414.64, "text": " vijatvam jayate nirunam"}, {"start": 414.64, "end": 416.64, "text": " rasa-vidhana"}, {"start": 416.64, "end": 420.64, "text": " and deeksha-vidhana"}, {"start": 420.64, "end": 422.64, "text": " This is a comparison made by"}, {"start": 422.64, "end": 424.64, "text": " Srila Sanatana Goswami,"}, {"start": 424.64, "end": 426.64, "text": " that just like"}, {"start": 426.64, "end": 432.64, "text": " the"}, {"start": 434.64, "end": 436.64, "text": " bell-metal"}, {"start": 436.64, "end": 439.64, "text": " can be turned into gold"}, {"start": 439.64, "end": 442.64, "text": " by chemical manipulation,"}, {"start": 442.64, "end": 444.64, "text": " by treating it with"}, {"start": 444.64, "end": 448.64, "text": " an alchemical process using mercury,"}, {"start": 448.64, "end": 453.64, "text": " rasa-vidhana."}, {"start": 453.64, "end": 455.64, "text": " Similarly,"}, {"start": 455.64, "end": 456.64, "text": " any person"}, {"start": 456.64, "end": 458.64, "text": " from any material background,"}, {"start": 458.64, "end": 461.64, "text": " how much ever contaminated he may be,"}, {"start": 461.64, "end": 462.64, "text": " if he undergoes"}, {"start": 462.64, "end": 466.64, "text": " the spiritual disciplinary actions"}, {"start": 466.64, "end": 467.64, "text": " under the guidance"}, {"start": 467.64, "end": 470.64, "text": " of a bona fide spiritual master,"}, {"start": 470.64, "end": 473.64, "text": " he can attain the perfection"}, {"start": 473.64, "end": 476.64, "text": " of a twice-born brahmana."}, {"start": 476.64, "end": 484.64, "text": " vijatvam jayate nirunam"}, {"start": 484.64, "end": 486.64, "text": " So, that process"}, {"start": 486.64, "end": 489.64, "text": " is described as sadhana bhakti."}, {"start": 489.64, "end": 491.64, "text": " sadhana bhakti."}, {"start": 492.64, "end": 493.64, "text": " And,"}, {"start": 493.64, "end": 495.64, "text": " it is given in the scriptures,"}, {"start": 495.64, "end": 496.64, "text": " anyone who adopts"}, {"start": 496.64, "end": 498.64, "text": " the process of sadhana bhakti"}, {"start": 498.64, "end": 500.64, "text": " under proper guidance"}, {"start": 500.64, "end": 504.64, "text": " of a bona fide spiritual master."}, {"start": 504.64, "end": 507.64, "text": " One cannot independently do anything"}, {"start": 507.64, "end": 509.64, "text": " in spiritual life, no."}, {"start": 509.64, "end": 511.64, "text": " You require the proper guidance"}, {"start": 511.64, "end": 514.64, "text": " of a bona fide spiritual master."}, {"start": 514.64, "end": 518.64, "text": " And under such expert guidance,"}, {"start": 518.64, "end": 520.64, "text": " strictly following the rules"}, {"start": 520.64, "end": 521.64, "text": " and regulations"}, {"start": 521.64, "end": 523.64, "text": " and the process,"}, {"start": 523.64, "end": 526.64, "text": " one becomes purified."}, {"start": 526.64, "end": 528.64, "text": " And that purification results in"}, {"start": 528.64, "end": 532.64, "text": " one becoming a perfect twice-born brahmana."}, {"start": 532.64, "end": 534.64, "text": " Perfection of a brahmana"}, {"start": 534.64, "end": 536.64, "text": " is to become a devotee."}, {"start": 536.64, "end": 540.64, "text": " So one becomes a devotee."}, {"start": 540.64, "end": 542.64, "text": " So Srila Prabhupada says,"}, {"start": 542.64, "end": 545.64, "text": " it is therefore the actual guidance"}, {"start": 545.64, "end": 546.64, "text": " that matters"}, {"start": 546.64, "end": 549.64, "text": " in the process of becoming a brahmana,"}, {"start": 549.64, "end": 551.64, "text": " even without change of body,"}, {"start": 551.64, "end": 552.64, "text": " or in going back to Godhead"}, {"start": 552.64, "end": 555.64, "text": " without change of body."}, {"start": 555.64, "end": 559.64, "text": " It is the actual guidance"}, {"start": 559.64, "end": 561.64, "text": " of an expert"}, {"start": 561.64, "end": 563.64, "text": " and engaging properly"}, {"start": 563.64, "end": 570.64, "text": " in the activities of sadhana bhakti."}, {"start": 570.64, "end": 574.64, "text": " Now, Srila Jeeva Goswami says here"}, {"start": 574.64, "end": 576.64, "text": " that the use of the word"}, {"start": 576.64, "end": 578.64, "text": " he in this connection"}, {"start": 578.64, "end": 581.64, "text": " positively affirms this truth."}, {"start": 581.64, "end": 583.64, "text": " What is the word?"}, {"start": 583.64, "end": 584.64, "text": " In the verse,"}, {"start": 584.64, "end": 586.64, "text": " virajena"}, {"start": 586.64, "end": 587.64, "text": " atmana"}, {"start": 587.64, "end": 588.64, "text": " eva"}, {"start": 588.64, "end": 589.64, "text": " he"}, {"start": 589.64, "end": 591.64, "text": " This word he,"}, {"start": 591.64, "end": 594.64, "text": " ending word of the"}, {"start": 594.64, "end": 597.64, "text": " 48th verse,"}, {"start": 597.64, "end": 599.64, "text": " that affirms positively"}, {"start": 599.64, "end": 601.64, "text": " this truth that"}, {"start": 601.64, "end": 604.64, "text": " there is no need to change body"}, {"start": 604.64, "end": 606.64, "text": " if one has to go back to Godhead"}, {"start": 606.64, "end": 608.64, "text": " after having executed"}, {"start": 608.64, "end": 610.64, "text": " pure devotional service."}, {"start": 611.64, "end": 617.64, "text": " So this fact is affirmed here."}, {"start": 617.64, "end": 620.64, "text": " And the Bhagavad Gita confirms this"}, {"start": 620.64, "end": 623.64, "text": " that anyone who systematically executes"}, {"start": 623.64, "end": 626.64, "text": " pure devotional service without deviation"}, {"start": 626.64, "end": 629.64, "text": " can attain this perfection of Brahman."}, {"start": 629.64, "end": 631.64, "text": " Brahman perfection needs"}, {"start": 631.64, "end": 633.64, "text": " to be situated on the spiritual platform"}, {"start": 633.64, "end": 635.64, "text": " above the three gunas."}, {"start": 635.64, "end": 637.64, "text": " And"}, {"start": 637.64, "end": 639.64, "text": " on the Brahman platform"}, {"start": 639.64, "end": 642.64, "text": " then one engages in pure devotional service."}, {"start": 642.64, "end": 644.64, "text": " Pure devotional service is only possible"}, {"start": 644.64, "end": 645.64, "text": " on the Brahman platform,"}, {"start": 645.64, "end": 648.64, "text": " on the spiritual platform."}, {"start": 648.64, "end": 651.64, "text": " Then one becomes"}, {"start": 651.64, "end": 654.64, "text": " completely perfect."}, {"start": 654.64, "end": 656.64, "text": " Becomes completely perfect."}, {"start": 656.64, "end": 658.64, "text": " And"}, {"start": 658.64, "end": 660.64, "text": " such a person actually"}, {"start": 660.64, "end": 662.64, "text": " is eligible"}, {"start": 662.64, "end": 664.64, "text": " to directly go"}, {"start": 664.64, "end": 666.64, "text": " to the spiritual world"}, {"start": 666.64, "end": 668.64, "text": " and that also the supreme planet,"}, {"start": 668.64, "end": 670.64, "text": " Koloka Vrindavana,"}, {"start": 670.64, "end": 672.64, "text": " without change of body."}, {"start": 675.64, "end": 677.64, "text": " Now this has already been explained"}, {"start": 677.64, "end": 679.64, "text": " by Srila Prabhupada"}, {"start": 679.64, "end": 681.64, "text": " in an earlier verse"}, {"start": 681.64, "end": 683.64, "text": " where it was said"}, {"start": 683.64, "end": 686.64, "text": " Lord Krishna returned to his own abode"}, {"start": 686.64, "end": 688.64, "text": " without a change of body."}, {"start": 688.64, "end": 692.64, "text": " Because Lord's body is completely transcendental."}, {"start": 692.64, "end": 694.64, "text": " Even when he comes to this world"}, {"start": 694.64, "end": 697.64, "text": " he comes in his original spiritual form."}, {"start": 698.64, "end": 703.64, "text": " Ajopisan avyayatma."}, {"start": 703.64, "end": 704.64, "text": " Avyayatma means"}, {"start": 704.64, "end": 706.64, "text": " Krishna never changes his body."}, {"start": 706.64, "end": 708.64, "text": " His body never deteriorates."}, {"start": 708.64, "end": 710.64, "text": " His body is always spiritual."}, {"start": 710.64, "end": 713.64, "text": " Material bodies are deteriorating."}, {"start": 713.64, "end": 715.64, "text": " They change."}, {"start": 715.64, "end": 717.64, "text": " And we have to quit this body"}, {"start": 717.64, "end": 719.64, "text": " at the time of death"}, {"start": 719.64, "end": 721.64, "text": " or at the end of this life"}, {"start": 721.64, "end": 723.64, "text": " or when we are"}, {"start": 723.64, "end": 725.64, "text": " when we are"}, {"start": 725.64, "end": 727.64, "text": " transferred to another body."}, {"start": 727.64, "end": 729.64, "text": " We have to quit this body."}, {"start": 729.64, "end": 732.64, "text": " But Krishna never accepts any material body."}, {"start": 732.64, "end": 735.64, "text": " He never comes in touch with matter."}, {"start": 735.64, "end": 737.64, "text": " He is always situated"}, {"start": 737.64, "end": 739.64, "text": " in his eternal spiritual form,"}, {"start": 739.64, "end": 741.64, "text": " spiritual body,"}, {"start": 741.64, "end": 743.64, "text": " which may be of different forms"}, {"start": 743.64, "end": 746.64, "text": " according to the need."}, {"start": 746.64, "end": 749.64, "text": " But all of them are the same spirit,"}, {"start": 749.64, "end": 753.64, "text": " same supreme Lord"}, {"start": 753.64, "end": 756.64, "text": " without any change."}, {"start": 756.64, "end": 759.64, "text": " The same supreme Lord."}, {"start": 759.64, "end": 764.64, "text": " So when Lord Krishna returns to his abode"}, {"start": 764.64, "end": 768.64, "text": " he returns in his personal form."}, {"start": 768.64, "end": 773.64, "text": " The same supreme spiritual form."}, {"start": 773.64, "end": 775.64, "text": " There is no change of body."}, {"start": 775.64, "end": 778.64, "text": " Similarly, pure devotees"}, {"start": 778.64, "end": 780.64, "text": " simply because they are engaged in"}, {"start": 780.64, "end": 782.64, "text": " pure devotional service"}, {"start": 782.64, "end": 784.64, "text": " always, constantly,"}, {"start": 784.64, "end": 786.64, "text": " 24 hours a day."}, {"start": 786.64, "end": 790.64, "text": " They don't change their body"}, {"start": 790.64, "end": 792.64, "text": " because their body"}, {"start": 792.64, "end": 794.64, "text": " is a spiritual one."}, {"start": 794.64, "end": 796.64, "text": " Spiritualized by"}, {"start": 796.64, "end": 798.64, "text": " pure devotional service."}, {"start": 798.64, "end": 800.64, "text": " Spiritualized by"}, {"start": 800.64, "end": 802.64, "text": " pure devotional service."}, {"start": 804.64, "end": 807.64, "text": " So, even if we practice"}, {"start": 807.64, "end": 809.64, "text": " constant chanting of"}, {"start": 809.64, "end": 811.64, "text": " Hare Krishna, Hare Krishna,"}, {"start": 811.64, "end": 813.64, "text": " Krishna Krishna, Hare Hare,"}, {"start": 813.64, "end": 815.64, "text": " Hare Rama, Hare Rama, Rama Rama,"}, {"start": 815.64, "end": 816.64, "text": " Hare Hare,"}, {"start": 816.64, "end": 818.64, "text": " then we don't have to"}, {"start": 818.64, "end": 820.64, "text": " change our body."}, {"start": 820.64, "end": 822.64, "text": " Our body becomes spiritualized"}, {"start": 822.64, "end": 824.64, "text": " by constantly engaging in chanting"}, {"start": 824.64, "end": 827.64, "text": " and hearing the holy name."}, {"start": 827.64, "end": 830.64, "text": " Just like iron in contact"}, {"start": 830.64, "end": 832.64, "text": " with fire"}, {"start": 832.64, "end": 836.64, "text": " becomes red hot and fire-like."}, {"start": 836.64, "end": 838.64, "text": " Similarly,"}, {"start": 838.64, "end": 840.64, "text": " of course this is a crude example,"}, {"start": 840.64, "end": 843.64, "text": " but in the case of our own"}, {"start": 843.64, "end": 844.64, "text": " material body,"}, {"start": 844.64, "end": 846.64, "text": " that we have now,"}, {"start": 846.64, "end": 849.64, "text": " it also becomes spiritualized"}, {"start": 849.64, "end": 853.64, "text": " by our engagement"}, {"start": 853.64, "end": 854.64, "text": " in devotional service,"}, {"start": 854.64, "end": 856.64, "text": " pure devotional service."}, {"start": 856.64, "end": 858.64, "text": " So I'll stop here."}, {"start": 858.64, "end": 859.64, "text": " Thank you very much."}, {"start": 859.64, "end": 860.64, "text": " Hare Krishna."}]}